name: r-origami
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = "1.0.5" %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-origami
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/origami_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/origami/origami_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 8d0d08aaecc428cbbf5db4615ad3623777c10c6d7947a1cc3ccc7f8db8cb5263

build:
  merge_build_host: true  # [win]
  number: 0
  noarch: generic
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ posix }}zip               # [win]
    - cross-r-base {{ r_base }}    # [build_platform != target_platform]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-abind
    - r-assertthat
    - r-data.table
    - r-future
    - r-future.apply
    - r-listenv
  run:
    - r-base
    - r-abind
    - r-assertthat
    - r-data.table
    - r-future
    - r-future.apply
    - r-listenv

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('origami')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('origami')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://tlverse.org/origami
  license: GPL-3.0-only
  summary: A general framework for the application of cross-validation schemes to particular functions. By allowing arbitrary lists of results, origami accommodates a range of cross-validation applications.
  license_family: GPL3
  license_file:
    - {{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/GPL-3

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r

# Package: origami
# Title: Generalized Framework for Cross-Validation
# Version: 1.0.3
